SRC_EQN: Kauffman, J.B., Martin, R.E. 1990. Sprouting shrub response to different seasons and fuel consumption levels of prescribed fire in Sierra Nevada mixed conifer ecosystems. Forest Science, v.36(3), p.748-764.

DEP_VAR: Volume, stem, bark (Assuming const. Bark:Diam rat)
DPV_O: Volume, stem, bark (Assuming const. Bark:diam ratio
ORG_EQFM: VSB = (pi*HT/3) * (R1^2- (R1-Barkthick)^2); where R1=DBA/2, barkthick=0.408 cm (midrange from Minore et al (1993).
RAW_DATA: BArk thickness data based on Minore et al 1993.  Volume formula is for a cone modified from Vance et al 1994 who used frustrum of a cone.
SRC_EQN: Derived by Joe Means:  Vance et al assumed bole form of frustrum of a cone and constant bark thickness up bole based on Minore et al 1993 finding of no variation in bark thickness in first 2 meters.  Bark = midrange of Minore et al 19

DEP_VAR: Volume, stem, bark (Assuming const. Bark:Diam rat)
DPV_O: Volume, stem, bark (Assuming const. Bark:diam ratio
RAW_DATA: Bark thickness data from Minore et al 1993.  Volume formula is for a cone modified from Vance et al 1994 who used frustrum of a cone.
SRC_EQN: Derived by Joe Means:  Vance et al assumed bole form of frustrum of a cone (6 trees) and constant bark thickness up bole based on Minore et al 1993 finding of no variation in bark thickness in first 2 meters.

DPV_O: Volume, stem, bark (Assuming const. Bark thickness)
ORG_EQFM: VSB = (pi*HT/3)*{R1^2+R1*R2+R2^2-[(R1-B)^2+(R1-B)(R2-B)+(R2-B)^2]};   where R1=DBA/2, R2=tip radius(0.25cm), B=bark thickness
RAW_DATA: Bark thickness data from Minore et al 1993.  Volume formula is for a cone frustrum following Vance et al 1994.
SRC_EQN: Derived by Joe Means:  Vance et al assumed bole form of frustrum of a cone (6 trees) and constant bark thickness up bole based on Minore et al 1993 finding of no variation in bark thickness in first 2 meters.

PA3_TEXT: Bark thickness (using Length param) at 30 cm ht
DPV_O: Volume, stem, bark (Assuming const. Bark thickness)
ORG_EQFM: VSB =(pi*HT/3)*{R1^2+R1*R2+R2^2-[(R1-B)^2+(R1-B)(R2-B)+(R2-B)^2]};  where R1=DBA/2, R2=tip radius, B=bark thickness
RAW_DATA: Bark thickness data from Minore et al 1993.  Volume formula is for a cone frustrum following Vance et al 1994.
SRC_EQN: Derived by Joe Means:  Vance et al assumed bole form of frustrum of a cone (6 trees) and constant bark thickness up bole based on Minore et al 1993 finding of no variation in bark thickness in first 2 meters.
